"use strict";(self.webpackChunkwebsite_new=self.webpackChunkwebsite_new||[]).push([[6896],{27888(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut","metadata":{"permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-24-rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut.md","title":"Rayforge 1.6 - Device Profiles, Rotary Overhaul, Print & Cut","description":"Rayforge 1.6 brings a complete rotary overhaul, device profiles, a redesigned layer system, per-layer WCS, and a Print and Cut addon.","date":"2026-04-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.6","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/1-6"},{"inline":true,"label":"rotary","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/rotary"},{"inline":true,"label":"device-profiles","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/device-profiles"},{"inline":true,"label":"print-and-cut","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/print-and-cut"},{"inline":true,"label":"layers","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/layers"}],"readingTime":2.6,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/es/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut","title":"Rayforge 1.6 - Device Profiles, Rotary Overhaul, Print & Cut","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.6","rotary","device-profiles","print-and-cut","layers"],"description":"Rayforge 1.6 brings a complete rotary overhaul, device profiles, a redesigned layer system, per-layer WCS, and a Print and Cut addon."},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.6 brings a complete rotary axis overhaul, a new device profile\\nsystem, a redesigned layer system with per-layer WCS, and a Print and Cut addon\\nfor aligning laser cuts with printed material.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Device Profiles\\n\\nMachine profiles have been replaced by **device profiles** -- declarative\\npackages that bundle your work area, axis setup, laser settings, and G-code\\ndialect into a single file. Pick your device and everything is pre-configured.\\nYou can export and import profiles to share setups between machines or back up\\nyour configuration.\\n\\n## Rotary Axis Overhaul\\n\\nRotary support was rewritten from the ground up with proper kinematics. The new\\nsystem supports a **true 4th axis** alongside your existing X, Y, and Z axes,\\nas well as **axis replacement mode** for setups where the rotary takes over X\\nor Y. Roller-type rotary attachments get their own dedicated settings.\\n\\nThe 2D canvas adapts to rotary mode automatically, and the 3D canvas renders\\nrotary toolpaths correctly in every configuration -- including during simulation\\nplayback. The kinematics engine was refactored to build dynamically from an axis\\nset and mapper, making it far more flexible and correct.\\n\\n## Print and Cut\\n\\nA new addon helps you align laser cuts with pre-printed material. Register\\nreference points on your print, let Rayforge calculate the offset and rotation,\\nand your cuts land exactly where they should. Perfect for making stickers,\\nlabels, or anything that needs to line up with an existing print.\\n\\n## Redesigned Layer System\\n\\nThe layer panel got a complete overhaul. Each layer column now shows a visual\\nworkflow so you can see your operations at a glance. You can reorder layers and\\nworkpieces with drag-and-drop. Each layer can be assigned its own Work\\nCoordinate System (G54-G59) for multi-fixture setups, with a quick edit button\\nright in the layer settings. The settings dialog is non-modal, so you can keep\\nit open while working on the canvas.\\n\\n## Material Test Grid\\n\\nNew parameter combinations are available, and multipass mode now shows extra\\nspeed or power labels so you can tell exactly what each cell represents.\\n\\n## GRBL Telnet Driver\\n\\nCommunity contributor gyordanov built a new driver that connects to GRBL\\ncontrollers over the network via Telnet. It works with grblHAL and ESP3D-based\\nboards -- no USB cable needed.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- **Update checker** notifies you when a new version is available\\n- **Floating properties panel** gives you more canvas space\\n- **Editable slider values** -- click and type the exact number you want\\n- **Ops color setting** -- choose layer color or laser color for rendering\\n- **Creality Falcon A1** device profile\\n- **Massively reduced memory** usage for multi-layer PDFs\\n- **GRBL serial improvements** with deadlock recovery and comment stripping\\n- **Sketcher** -- support changing text color using the fill tool\\n- **Canvas** -- right-click context menu for empty space\\n- **Windows** -- terminal window no longer appears on startup\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\nold-man-and-the-seam, Amsel, froqstar, pghpete, Derek McTavish, and four\\nanonymous supporters.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.6\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones","metadata":{"permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-09-rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones.md","title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","description":"Rayforge 1.5 adds a full 3D job simulator with playback controls, native cubic bezier G5 support, no-go zones with collision checking, and major performance gains.","date":"2026-04-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.5","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/1-5"},{"inline":true,"label":"simulator","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/simulator"},{"inline":true,"label":"bezier","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/bezier"},{"inline":true,"label":"nogozones","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/nogozones"},{"inline":true,"label":"performance","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/performance"}],"readingTime":3.34,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/es/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones","title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.5","simulator","bezier","nogozones","performance"],"description":"Rayforge 1.5 adds a full 3D job simulator with playback controls, native cubic bezier G5 support, no-go zones with collision checking, and major performance gains."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.6 - Device Profiles, Rotary Overhaul, Print & Cut","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.6-device-profiles-rotary-print-cut"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.5 adds a full 3D job simulator with playback controls, native\\ncubic bezier curve support (G5), no-go zones with collision checking, and\\nsignificant performance and memory improvements.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## 3D Simulator\\n\\nThe 3D canvas now has a complete job simulator. You can watch your job execute\\nstep by step -- the laser head moves along the toolpath, the beam appears when\\nthe laser fires, and bitmap engravings are progressively revealed as the\\nplayhead advances.\\n\\nPlayback controls sit at the bottom of the canvas: play/pause, step forward\\nand backward, a scrubber slider, and a speed button that cycles through 1x\\nto 16x. Rotary mode works too -- the cylinder rotates along with the\\nsimulation. All of this runs without blocking the rest of the interface, even\\non complex jobs.\\n\\n## Bezier Curves (G5)\\n\\nRayforge now supports native cubic bezier curves through the entire pipeline --\\nfrom import all the way to G-code output. For machines running LinuxCNC or\\nMarlin, curves are emitted as G5 commands instead of thousands of tiny line\\nsegments. The result is smoother cuts, smaller G-code files, and faster\\nexecution. For machines that don\'t support G5 (Grbl, Smoothieware, and\\nothers), curves are automatically linearized -- no configuration needed.\\n\\nThis touched nearly every part of the system. Tabs, cropping, smoothing,\\nmulti-pass, and path optimization all handle curves properly now.\\n\\n## No-Go Zones\\n\\nYou can now define restricted areas in your machine settings. These mark areas\\non the bed where the laser should not cut -- clamps, fixtures, or that corner\\nwhere the hose always gets in the way. Rayforge checks for collisions and warns\\nyou before sending G-code.\\n\\n## Performance and Memory\\n\\nThe canvas is significantly more responsive. When you drag, pan, or zoom,\\nexpensive laser-path rendering is suppressed until you stop moving -- no more\\nstuttering while repositioning a workpiece. Multi-step workflows render faster\\nbecause all visible steps are composited into a single surface.\\n\\nLarge images that used to cause multi-gigabyte memory spikes are now\\nautomatically scaled to sensible limits. The image handling was rewritten to\\navoid unnecessary copies, and caching is smarter -- shared images are rendered\\nonce and reused across workpieces. Two memory leaks in the 3D simulator were\\nalso fixed.\\n\\n## Dockable Bottom Panel\\n\\nThe bottom panel tabs can now be rearranged freely. Drag a tab onto the divider\\nbetween columns to split it off into its own column. You can keep the layer\\nlist and G-code viewer visible side by side, for example. The layout persists\\nbetween sessions.\\n\\n## Asset Browser\\n\\nThe asset browser has been overhauled. All assets are visible and can be\\ndragged to the canvas or to a specific layer. Multi-selection works for\\ndrag-and-drop and bulk deletion. Thumbnails are generated for most image\\nformats, and when the browser is empty it shows a helpful placeholder with\\nbuttons to add stock or a sketch.\\n\\n## New Import Options\\n\\nThe import dialog offers three layer modes: flatten into the current layer,\\ncreate new layers from the file, or map imported layers onto existing ones.\\nAfter import, Rayforge adds sensible default workflow steps -- a Contour step\\nfor vector layers and an Engrave step for layers with fills.\\n\\n## Lead-In / Lead-Out\\n\\nA new lead-in/lead-out postprocessor adds zero-power approach and exit moves\\nat the start and end of each contour. This helps the laser reach constant\\nvelocity before the actual cut begins, improving cut quality at entry and exit\\npoints.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- 3D model support for rotary axes (GLB format)\\n- Continuous laser mode and modal feedrate G-code options\\n- GRBL raster dialect with cleaner M4/M5 handling\\n- Grbl MKS DLC32 machine profile\\n- Material test: labels engraved first, overscan support, label speed setting\\n- Ctrl+F search in console and G-code viewer\\n- YUYV camera protocol support\\n- Addons can register toggles in the View menu\\n- Status bar removed, info moved to contextual locations\\n- Single instance lock\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.5\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera","metadata":{"permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-29-rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera.md","title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","description":"Rayforge 1.4 adds rotary axis support for cylindrical workpieces, PDF vector import with layers, camera calibration, and improved sketcher tools.","date":"2026-03-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.4","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/1-4"},{"inline":true,"label":"rotary","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/rotary"},{"inline":true,"label":"camera","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/camera"},{"inline":true,"label":"pdf","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/pdf"},{"inline":true,"label":"sketcher","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/sketcher"}],"readingTime":2.87,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/es/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera","title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.4","rotary","camera","pdf","sketcher"],"description":"Rayforge 1.4 adds rotary axis support for cylindrical workpieces, PDF vector import with layers, camera calibration, and improved sketcher tools."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.5 - 3D Simulator, Bezier Curves, No-Go Zones","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.5-3d-simulator-bezier-nogozones"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.4 adds rotary axis support for cylindrical workpieces, direct\\nvector import for PDF files with layers, a guided camera calibration wizard,\\nand an improved sketcher with ellipse tools and smarter snapping.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Rotary Axis Support\\n\\nYou can now engrave and cut cylindrical objects like tumblers, glasses, and\\npens. Rayforge wraps your design around the cylinder surface and shows a 3D\\npreview so you know exactly what the result will look like before you start.\\n\\nRotary mode can be toggled per layer, which means you can combine flat and\\ncylindrical work in a single project. A small rotary icon next to each layer\\nmakes it easy to see which layers will run on the rotary attachment.\\n\\nHead over to the [Rotary Setup](../docs/machine/rotary) page for details on\\nconfiguring your module.\\n\\n## PDF Import with Layers\\n\\nPDF files can now be imported as vector paths instead of being rasterized\\nfirst. This means cleaner lines, no quality loss, and \u2014 if the PDF contains\\nlayers \u2014 you can pick which layers to import, just like with SVG files.\\n\\nThis is especially handy when someone sends you a PDF that was exported from\\nIllustrator or Inkscape and you need clean cutting paths without re-drawing\\nanything.\\n\\n## Camera Calibration Wizard\\n\\nGetting a camera aligned to your laser bed just got easier. The new guided\\ncalibration wizard walks you through the process step by step using a printed\\ncalibration card. Rayforge computes a full distortion model from the card\\nimages, correcting for barrel distortion and perspective errors automatically.\\n\\nThe result is noticeably better alignment accuracy, especially with wide-angle\\nlenses or cameras mounted at an angle.\\n\\n## Sketcher Improvements\\n\\nThe circle tool has been replaced with a more general **ellipse tool** that\\nhandles both circles and ellipses. The equality constraint now works on\\nellipses too.\\n\\nDrawing geometry also feels smoother now: many tools automatically apply\\nconstraints as you create shapes, and a new **magnetic snap** system replaces\\nthe old snap-to-grid behavior. Instead of locking to a fixed grid, magnetic\\nsnap pulls your cursor toward nearby geometry \u2014 points, lines, and endpoints \u2014\\nmaking it much easier to connect shapes precisely.\\n\\n## Better Framing Controls\\n\\nThe framing feature has new settings for finer control:\\n\\n- **Frame speed** is now configured per laser head\\n- **Corner dwell time** lets the laser pause briefly at each corner so you can\\n  see exactly where the boundary is\\n- **Repeat count** traces the outline multiple times for better visibility\\n\\n## Merge Lines Post-Processor\\n\\nA new post-processor called **Merge Lines** detects overlapping path segments\\nand merges them into a single pass. This is useful when you import designs\\nwhere shapes share edges \u2014 think grid patterns or tessellations \u2014 and you want\\nto avoid cutting the same line twice.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- Machine profile for the Acmer S1 has been added\\n- G-code dialects are now independent copies, so customizing one never affects\\n  others\\n- Dialects support a separate laser-on command for focusing\\n- Large images are handled more safely to prevent running out of memory\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\n- Fixed material test producer issues\\n- Fixed position reporting for machines with only X and Y axes\\n- Fixed a sketcher issue where distance constraints could shadow the line\\n  underneath\\n- Fixed memory exhaustion when importing very large images\\n- Fixed a race condition during worker initialization\\n\\nSee the CHANGELOG on GitHub for the complete list.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.4\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon","metadata":{"permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-23-rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon.md","title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","description":"Rayforge 1.3 adds bezier curve support in the sketcher, a unified path tool, more efficient G-code output, and moves the sketcher to an add-on.","date":"2026-03-23T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.3","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/1-3"},{"inline":true,"label":"sketcher","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/sketcher"},{"inline":true,"label":"bezier","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/bezier"},{"inline":true,"label":"addons","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/addons"}],"readingTime":2.68,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/es/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon","title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.3","sketcher","bezier","addons"],"description":"Rayforge 1.3 adds bezier curve support in the sketcher, a unified path tool, more efficient G-code output, and moves the sketcher to an add-on."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.4 - Rotary Axis, PDF Layers, Camera Calibration","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.4-rotary-pdf-camera"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.3 brings bezier curve support to the parametric sketcher, a new\\nunified path tool, more efficient G-code output, and moves the sketcher to\\nan optional add-on.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Bezier Curves in the Sketcher\\n\\nThe headline feature for this release is full support for bezier curves in\\nthe parametric sketcher. The old line tool has been replaced with a new\\nunified **path tool** that seamlessly combines lines and curves.\\n\\nYou can now:\\n\\n- Draw smooth bezier curves with intuitive handle-based editing\\n- Connect curves to existing geometry - the path edit tool can snap to\\n  existing points in your sketch\\n- Make endpoints smooth or symmetric when they\'re connected by a coincident\\n  constraint - perfect for creating seamless curves\\n- Convert bezier curves back to straight lines with the new \\"straighten\\"\\n  tool\\n\\nThis has been one of the most requested features, and we\'re excited to see\\nwhat you create with it.\\n\\n## Sketcher is Now an Add-on\\n\\nContinuing the modularization work from version 1.2, the sketcher has been\\nmoved to an add-on. It\'s installed and enabled by default, so existing users\\nwon\'t notice any difference. But if you prefer a minimal setup without\\nparametric sketching, you can now disable it.\\n\\nThis change also comes with new extension registries that make it easier for\\nadd-on developers to extend Rayforge.\\n\\n## Sketcher Quality-of-Life Improvements\\n\\nThe sketcher received several smaller but impactful improvements:\\n\\n**Grid Tool**\\nA new tool to toggle grid visibility for better alignment.\\n\\n**Conflicting Constraints**\\nWhen constraints conflict with each other, they\'re now highlighted in the\\npanel so you can quickly identify and fix the problem.\\n\\n**Show/Hide Controls**\\nNew toggle buttons let you show or hide construction geometry and constraints\\nindividually.\\n\\n**Shift Constrains Movement**\\nHold Shift while dragging to constrain movement to the nearest axis - great\\nfor keeping things aligned.\\n\\n**Cleaner Background**\\nThe gray background area is now hidden for a cleaner editing experience.\\n\\n## More Efficient G-code\\n\\nRayforge now produces more compact G-code by omitting unchanged coordinates.\\nIf you\'re cutting along the X-axis, for example, only the X coordinate will\\nbe emitted on each line. This makes files smaller and cleaner, and makes\\nthe old \\"no-Z\\" dialect variants obsolete (they\'ve been removed).\\n\\nThe G-code viewer also got some updates:\\n\\n- Shows line count and byte size\\n- Always displays at least the first 20,000 lines\\n\\n## Raster Operation Enhancements\\n\\nNew settings for sample interval and power levels give you more control over\\nyour raster operations. These are particularly useful for fine-tuning results\\non materials that need precise power management.\\n\\n## Other Improvements\\n\\n- All icons normalized to 32x32 viewbox for consistent appearance\\n- AI workpiece generator now creates sketches when the geometry can be mapped\\n- Updated translations\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\nThis release fixes many issues:\\n\\n- Fixed fillet and chamfer tools not working correctly\\n- Fixed texture encoder drawing spaced dots instead of lines in some cases\\n- Fixed G1 being emitted without coordinates when all coordinates were unchanged\\n- Fixed loading project files with unknown assets\\n- Fixed issues when disabling and re-enabling add-ons at runtime\\n\\nSee the CHANGELOG on GitHub for the complete list.\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.3\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](/docs/getting-started/installation)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai","metadata":{"permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-10-rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai.md","title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","description":"Rayforge 1.2 adds an AI workpiece generator for laser design, camera calibration improvements, and a modular add-on system for laser cutting workflows.","date":"2026-03-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.2","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/1-2"},{"inline":true,"label":"addons","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/addons"},{"inline":true,"label":"camera","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/camera"},{"inline":true,"label":"ai","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/ai"}],"readingTime":3.36,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/es/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai","title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.2","addons","camera","ai"],"description":"Rayforge 1.2 adds an AI workpiece generator for laser design, camera calibration improvements, and a modular add-on system for laser cutting workflows."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.3 - Bezier Curves in Sketcher, Modular Architecture","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.3-bezier-curves-sketcher-addon"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite"}},"content":"Rayforge 1.2 brings an AI workpiece generator, significant camera\\nenhancements, and a completely revamped add-on system with core\\nfunctionality now available as optional modules.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## AI Workpiece Generator Add-on\\n\\nA new experimental add-on allows generating workpieces from text prompts.\\nThis is great for quickly creating simple designs or getting inspiration\\nfor new projects.\\n\\nThis is a first step, and we\'re excited about the possibilities this\\nopens up for the future!\\n\\n## Camera Enhancements\\n\\nThanks to the incredible work of **MausRundung**, the camera system has\\nreceived a major overhaul:\\n\\n### Image Enhancement\\n\\n- Temporal noise reduction with configurable strength\\n- Cleaner preview images, especially in low-light conditions\\n\\n### Fisheye Distortion Correction\\n\\n- Radial distortion correction (k1, k2 parameters)\\n- Tangential distortion correction (p1, p2 parameters)\\n- Perfect for wide-angle lenses\\n\\n### Improved Alignment UI\\n\\n- Zoom, pan, and keyboard navigation in the alignment dialog\\n- Better point dragging with visual feedback\\n- Image stretching and positioning controls with offsets\\n\\n## Improved Add-on System\\n\\nThe add-on system has been greatly improved. The main change is that much\\nof the core functionality has been moved into add-ons that are installed\\nby default, but can be disabled or enabled as needed:\\n\\n**Core as Add-ons**\\nThe built-in transformers and laser essentials have been converted to\\nadd-ons. This makes Rayforge more modular - you can disable features you\\ndon\'t need or enable only what you want.\\n\\n**Add-on Capabilities**\\nAdd-ons can now:\\n- Register transformers (post-processors) for custom G-code manipulation\\n- Register keyboard shortcuts for custom workflows\\n- Hook into the backend and frontend independently\\n\\n**Commercial Support**\\nThe system now supports paid and third-party add-ons, enabling developers\\nto create commercial extensions for Rayforge.\\n\\n## Stock Improvements\\n\\nStock handling is now more flexible:\\n\\n- **Document-level stock** - stock is no longer tied to individual layers\\n- **Duplicate stock** using Ctrl+D\\n- **Non-rectangular stock** - convert any workpiece to stock for irregular\\n  materials\\n\\n## Sketcher Improvements\\n\\nThe parametric sketcher received several quality-of-life improvements in\\nthis release:\\n\\n- **Live preview for line tool** - see the line before you commit\\n- **Dimension display** - shows dimensions while adding geometry\\n- **Snap-to-grid** - hold Ctrl to snap to the grid\\n- **Entity highlighting** - hovered entities and constraints are highlighted\\n- **Toolbar shortcuts** - shows currently available keyboard shortcuts\\n- **Connected selection** - Shift+Double click selects connected geometry\\n- **Arc radius adjustment** - change arc radius while adding the second endpoint\\n\\n## More New Features\\n\\n### Crop to Stock Post-Processor\\n\\nA new post-processor that automatically crops operations to your stock\\nboundaries, saving time and material.\\n\\n### Inter-Workpiece Path Optimization\\n\\nThe path optimizer now also optimizes the workpiece order, reducing travel\\ndistance when working with multiple workpieces in a single job. Previously,\\nRayforge only optimized travel paths within individual workpieces.\\n\\n### Configurable Cut/Raster Colors\\n\\nEach laser can now have its own cut and raster colors, making it easier\\nto distinguish between different laser heads.\\n\\n### Quick WCS Positioning\\n\\nClick anywhere on the canvas to set the work coordinate system origin.\\n\\n### OMTech K40+ Profile\\n\\nNew machine profile for the popular OMTech K40+ laser cutter.\\n\\n### Mach4 G-code Dialect\\n\\nNew built-in G-code dialect for Mach4 controllers using M67 for spindle\\nspeed (laser power) control.\\n\\n### Platform Updates\\n\\n- Updated macOS support thanks to **Pablo Gil**\\n- Flatpak updates thanks to **fllmn**\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\nThis release addresses many issues:\\n\\n- Add-on not enabled immediately after installation\\n- macOS bundle issues with GTK modules and built-in add-ons\\n- Tasker startup crash with DictProxy type annotations\\n- Old project files not showing new transformers\\n- SVG exporter stacking multiple workpieces on top of each other\\n- Auto layout for rotated stock\\n- Windows build using wrong version string on forks\\n- Mac and Windows builds not finding icon\\n\\nSee the CHANGELOG on GitHub for the complete list.\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\n\\n- 2 anonymous contributors\\n- Amsel\\n- froqstar\\n\\nAnd thanks to **MausRundung** for the camera enhancements, **Pablo Gil** for\\nmacOS updates, and **fllmn** for Flatpak updates!\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.2\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/releases)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite","metadata":{"permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-27-rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite.md","title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","description":"Rayforge 1.1 brings macOS support, a new G-code console, unified raster operations, and a rewritten pipeline for better laser cutting performance.","date":"2026-02-27T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1.1","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/1-1"},{"inline":true,"label":"pipeline","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/pipeline"},{"inline":true,"label":"raster","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/raster"},{"inline":true,"label":"gcode","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/gcode"}],"readingTime":2.48,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/es/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite","title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1.1","pipeline","raster","gcode"],"description":"Rayforge 1.1 brings macOS support, a new G-code console, unified raster operations, and a rewritten pipeline for better laser cutting performance."},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.2 - AI Generator, Camera Enhancements, and Improved Add-ons","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.2-addons-camera-ai"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.0 - Una Celebraci\xf3n del Primer Cumplea\xf1os","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.0-first-birthday"}},"content":"![Rayforge 1.1](/images/rayforge-1.1.png)\\n\\nRayforge 1.1 brings a powerful new G-code console, unified raster operations,\\nand a completely rebuilt data pipeline for improved performance and stability.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## MacOS Support\\n\\nThanks to the incredible work of GitHub user **pgilfernandez**, Rayforge\\nnow officially supports macOS! Both Intel and Apple Silicon Macs are\\nsupported. This has been a long-requested feature, and we\'re thrilled to\\nwelcome Mac users to the Rayforge community.\\n\\n## The Big Story: Complete Pipeline Rewrite\\n\\nThe headline feature of this release is a complete rewrite of the data\\npipeline backend. The new architecture is based on a Directed Acyclic Graph\\n(DAG), which brings significant improvements:\\n\\n- **Better performance** for complex projects with many operations\\n- **Reduced memory usage** through more efficient data handling\\n- **Smoother UI responsiveness** during heavy processing\\n- **Fixed memory leaks** that affected long editing sessions\\n\\nThis foundational upgrade makes Rayforge more robust and prepares the\\ncodebase for future features.\\n\\n## Unified Raster Operations\\n\\nThe old \\"raster\\", \\"depth\\", and \\"dither\\" operations have been merged into a\\nsingle, unified raster operation. This simplifies the workflow while giving\\nyou more control:\\n\\n- **Configurable line distance** in all raster operations\\n- **New \\"Raster (Dither)\\" operation** with configurable algorithms\\n- **Auto thresholding** for Variable Power and Multipass modes\\n- **Histogram** in the raster engraver for visual threshold setting\\n- **Symbolic visualization** of raster direction in the rasterizer\\n\\n## G-code Console\\n\\nThe log view has been replaced with a fully-featured G-code terminal. You can\\nnow send commands directly to your machine, view responses in real-time, and\\ninteract with your laser cutter more directly than ever before.\\n\\n## More New Features\\n\\n### Export Support\\n\\nYou can now export your documents or selected objects to SVG and DXF formats.\\nThis is great for sharing designs or using them in other software.\\n\\n### Sketcher Improvements\\n\\n- **Angle constraints** are now available in the parametric sketcher\\n- **Conflicting constraints** are highlighted in red for easier debugging\\n\\n### Machine Configuration\\n\\n- Axis extents, work surface, and soft limits can now be configured per machine\\n- Built-in G-code dialect supporting dynamic power mode\\n\\n### Other Additions\\n\\n- Increased maximum laser spot size to 10 mm\\n- `RAYFORGE_MAX_WORKERS` environment variable to limit processes\\n- macOS packaging scripts and resources for better platform support\\n- `--uiscript` CLI argument for executing scripts after the UI is up\\n\\n## Bug Fixes\\n\\nThis release addresses many issues:\\n\\n- Multiple memory leaks in the data pipeline\\n- Race conditions between worker pool task completion and pipeline shutdown\\n- Camera device scanning crash on Windows\\n- Multipass post-processor exception\\n- Rasterizer angle causing distortion\\n- Various macOS issues: shm_open length errors, SVG rendering fallback,\\n  keyboard shortcuts\\n- Workpiece stage not emitting correct node state\\n- Zoom resolution stuck until resizing at least once\\n- Blurry view overlay on startup\\n- Unresponsive serial ports now handled gracefully\\n\\n## Special Thanks\\n\\nThis release was made possible with the support of our Patreon supporters:\\n\\n- 2 anonymous contributors\\n- Amsel\\n\\nThank you for supporting Rayforge development!\\n\\n## Download Rayforge 1.1\\n\\n- [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/releases)\\n- [Website](https://rayforge.org/)\\n\\n## Join the Community\\n\\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ)\\n- [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap)"},{"id":"rayforge-1.0-first-birthday","metadata":{"permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.0-first-birthday","source":"@site/i18n/es/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2026-01-29-rayforge-1.0-first-birthday.md","title":"Rayforge 1.0 - Una Celebraci\xf3n del Primer Cumplea\xf1os","description":"Rayforge 1.0","date":"2026-01-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"release","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/release"},{"inline":true,"label":"1","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/1"},{"inline":true,"label":"milestone","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/milestone"}],"readingTime":3.6,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/es/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"rayforge-1.0-first-birthday","title":"Rayforge 1.0 - Una Celebraci\xf3n del Primer Cumplea\xf1os","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["release","1","milestone"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.1 - MacOS Support, Pipeline Rewrite, G-code Console, and Unified Raster","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.1-pipeline-rewrite"},"nextItem":{"title":"5 Consejos para Mejores Resultados de Grabado L\xe1ser con Rayforge","permalink":"/es/blog/5-tips-better-engraving"}},"content":"![Rayforge 1.0](/images/rayforge-1.0.png)\\n\\nHoy marca un hito especial para Rayforge\u2014estamos lanzando la versi\xf3n 1.0 exactamente en el primer cumplea\xf1os del proyecto. Lo que comenz\xf3 como un solo commit el 1 de febrero de 2025, se ha convertido en una plataforma completa de corte y grabado l\xe1ser.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## El Camino Recorrido\\n\\nDurante el \xfaltimo a\xf1o, Rayforge ha evolucionado de una herramienta b\xe1sica de control l\xe1ser a una plataforma integral de dise\xf1o y manufactura. Hemos construido todo desde cero: un sistema CAD 2D param\xe9trico, vista previa 3D de G-code, soporte multicapa, soporte multi-l\xe1ser, alineaci\xf3n con c\xe1mara, sistemas de coordenadas de trabajo, y mucho m\xe1s.\\n\\nEste lanzamiento representa la culminaci\xf3n de esa visi\xf3n\u2014una herramienta estable y lista para producci\xf3n que puede manejar flujos de trabajo reales de corte y grabado l\xe1ser.\\n\\n## Qu\xe9 hay Nuevo en 1.0\\n\\n### Guardar/Cargar Proyectos\\n\\nLa funci\xf3n m\xe1s solicitada finalmente est\xe1 aqu\xed. Ahora puedes guardar tus flujos de trabajo completos y restaurarlos m\xe1s tarde. Las extensiones de archivo `.ryp` (proyecto) y `.rfs` (bosquejo) est\xe1n registradas en todo el sistema, por lo que puedes hacer doble clic en tus proyectos para abrirlos directamente. Un men\xfa de archivos recientes proporciona acceso r\xe1pido a tu trabajo.\\n\\n### Bosquejador Param\xe9trico con Soporte de Texto\\n\\nEl bosquejador ahora soporta texto con integraci\xf3n completa de restricciones. Agrega texto a tus bosquejos, aplica restricciones de relaci\xf3n de aspecto, y controla la ubicaci\xf3n y el tama\xf1o param\xe9tricamente. Esto abre todo un nuevo mundo de posibilidades de dise\xf1o para letreros grabados con l\xe1ser, etiquetas y elementos decorativos.\\n\\n### Panel Inferior Unificado\\n\\nEl di\xe1logo de jog y la vista de registro se han fusionado en un solo panel inferior unificado. Esta consolidaci\xf3n proporciona un espacio de trabajo m\xe1s limpio mientras mantiene las herramientas esenciales de control y monitoreo de la m\xe1quina f\xe1cilmente accesibles. El panel presenta acceso con pesta\xf1as a los controles de jog y la salida del registro, facilitando el cambio entre operaciones sin perder espacio en pantalla.\\n\\n### Otras Mejoras\\n\\n- **Panel inferior**: El di\xe1logo de jog y la vista de registro ahora est\xe1n fusionados en un panel inferior unificado\\n- **Di\xe1logo de importaci\xf3n**: Los errores ahora se recopilan y muestran juntos\\n- **Importadores**: Casi completamente reescritos para mejor capacidad de prueba\\n- **Estabilidad del bosquejador**: El solver ahora sesga los puntos para un arrastre m\xe1s estable\\n- **Correcciones de errores**: Importaci\xf3n DXF multicapa, errores de alineaci\xf3n, problemas de centrado, y m\xe1s\\n\\n## Funciones Destacadas\\n\\nRayforge 1.0 incluye m\xe1s de 60 funciones:\\n\\n**Herramientas de Dise\xf1o**\\n\\n- CAD 2D con bosquejo param\xe9trico\\n- Restricciones geom\xe9tricas y dimensionales\\n- Soporte de texto en bosquejos\\n- Soporte multicapa\\n\\n**Manufactura**\\n\\n- Operaciones 2.5D (contorno, raster, grabado de profundidad)\\n- Soporte multi-l\xe1ser\\n- Sistemas de Coordenadas de Trabajo (G54-G59)\\n- Optimizaci\xf3n y suavizado de trayectorias\\n- Pesta\xf1as de sujeci\xf3n con colocaci\xf3n autom\xe1tica\\n\\n**Importar/Exportar**\\n\\n- Soporte para archivos SVG, DXF, PDF, JPEG, PNG, BMP, Ruida\\n- Trazado vectorial con m\xfaltiples algoritmos\\n- Preprocesamiento de im\xe1genes (reducci\xf3n de ruido, invertir, umbral)\\n\\n**Control de M\xe1quina**\\n\\n- Perfiles multi-m\xe1quina\\n- Configuraci\xf3n de firmware para GRBL, Smoothieware, Marlin\\n- Macros y ganchos de G-code\\n- Sustituci\xf3n de variables\\n- Consola de terminal con estado en vivo\\n\\n**Visualizaci\xf3n**\\n\\n- Vista previa 3D de G-code con simulaci\xf3n completa\\n- Alineaci\xf3n con c\xe1mara\\n- Temas oscuro y claro\\n- Soporte multi-idioma\\n\\n## Un Vistazo Atr\xe1s\\n\\nEl primer commit se hizo el 1 de febrero de 2025, a las 19:37:27. Fue un simple \\"initial import\\" con soporte b\xe1sico de renderizado SVG. Desde entonces, hemos:\\n\\n- Lanzado 28 versiones (0.13 hasta 0.28, m\xe1s 1.0)\\n- Agregado m\xe1s de 60 funciones\\n- Corregido cientos de errores\\n- Construido una comunidad de usuarios y colaboradores\\n- Creado instaladores para Windows, Linux (deb, snap, flatpak) y macOS\\n\\n## \xbfQu\xe9 Sigue?\\n\\nLa versi\xf3n 1.0 es un hito, no un destino. La hoja de ruta adelante incluye:\\n\\n- Herramientas vectoriales mejoradas y capacidades de edici\xf3n\\n- Soporte de hardware m\xe1s amplio\\n- Optimizaciones de rendimiento para proyectos grandes\\n- M\xe1s perfiles de m\xe1quina y dialectos\\n- Ecosistema de paquetes impulsado por la comunidad\\n\\n## Descarga Rayforge 1.0\\n\\nObt\xe9n la \xfaltima versi\xf3n desde nuestro sitio web: https://rayforge.org/\\n\\nLos instaladores est\xe1n disponibles para:\\n\\n- Windows (instalador)\\n- Linux (deb, snap, flatpak)\\n- macOS (dmg)\\n\\n## \xdanete a la Comunidad\\n\\n- **GitHub**: https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge\\n- **Discord**: https://discord.gg/sTHNdTtpQJ\\n- **Patreon**: https://www.patreon.com/c/knipknap\\n\\nGracias a todos los que han contribuido, probado, reportado errores, o simplemente usado Rayforge durante este \xfaltimo a\xf1o. \xa1Brindemos por otro a\xf1o construyendo el futuro de la manufactura de c\xf3digo abierto!\\n\\n---\\n\\n*\xa1Feliz primer cumplea\xf1os, Rayforge! \ud83c\udf82*"},{"id":"5-tips-better-engraving","metadata":{"permalink":"/es/blog/5-tips-better-engraving","source":"@site/i18n/es/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-02-20-5-tips-better-engraving.md","title":"5 Consejos para Mejores Resultados de Grabado L\xe1ser con Rayforge","description":"3D Preview","date":"2025-02-20T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"engraving","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/engraving"},{"inline":true,"label":"optimization","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/optimization"},{"inline":true,"label":"quality","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/quality"},{"inline":true,"label":"workflow","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/workflow"}],"readingTime":4.04,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/es/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"5-tips-better-engraving","title":"5 Consejos para Mejores Resultados de Grabado L\xe1ser con Rayforge","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["engraving","optimization","quality","workflow"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rayforge 1.0 - Una Celebraci\xf3n del Primer Cumplea\xf1os","permalink":"/es/blog/rayforge-1.0-first-birthday"},"nextItem":{"title":"Soporte Multi-L\xe1ser - Elige Diferentes L\xe1seres para Cada Operaci\xf3n","permalink":"/es/blog/multi-laser-support"}},"content":"![3D Preview](/screenshots/main-3d.png)\\n\\nObtener resultados de grabado l\xe1ser de calidad profesional requiere m\xe1s que solo buen hardware\u2014tu configuraci\xf3n de software y flujo de trabajo tambi\xe9n importan. Aqu\xed hay cinco consejos para ayudarte a aprovechar al m\xe1ximo Rayforge.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## 1. Usa Overscan para un Grabado Raster M\xe1s Suave\\n\\nAl hacer grabado raster, un problema com\xfan es ver l\xedneas visibles o inconsistencias en los bordes donde el l\xe1ser cambia de direcci\xf3n. Esto sucede porque la cabeza del l\xe1ser necesita desacelerar y acelerar, lo que puede afectar la calidad del grabado.\\n\\n**Soluci\xf3n**: Activa **Overscan** en la configuraci\xf3n de tu operaci\xf3n raster.\\n\\nOverscan extiende la trayectoria de viaje del l\xe1ser m\xe1s all\xe1 del \xe1rea de grabado real, permitiendo que la cabeza alcance la velocidad m\xe1xima antes de entrar al \xe1rea de trabajo y mantenga esa velocidad durante todo el recorrido. Esto resulta en un grabado mucho m\xe1s suave y consistente.\\n\\nPara activar overscan:\\n\\n1. Selecciona tu operaci\xf3n raster\\n2. Abre la configuraci\xf3n de la operaci\xf3n\\n3. Activa \\"Overscan\\" y establece la distancia (t\xedpicamente 3-5mm funciona bien)\\n\\nAprende m\xe1s en nuestra [gu\xeda de Overscan](/docs/features/overscan).\\n\\n## 2. Optimiza el Tiempo de Desplazamiento con Ordenamiento de Trayectorias\\n\\nPara operaciones de contorno con muchas trayectorias separadas, el orden en que el l\xe1ser visita cada forma puede impactar significativamente el tiempo total del trabajo.\\n\\n**Soluci\xf3n**: Usa la **optimizaci\xf3n del tiempo de desplazamiento** integrada de Rayforge.\\n\\nRayforge puede reordenar autom\xe1ticamente las trayectorias para minimizar el tiempo de desplazamiento sin corte. Esto es especialmente \xfatil para trabajos con muchos objetos peque\xf1os o texto con m\xfaltiples letras.\\n\\nLa optimizaci\xf3n de trayectorias t\xedpicamente est\xe1 activada por defecto, pero puedes verificarla y ajustarla en la configuraci\xf3n de la operaci\xf3n Contour.\\n\\n## 3. Agrega Pesta\xf1as de Sujeci\xf3n para Prevenir el Movimiento de Piezas\\n\\nNada es m\xe1s frustrante que tener un trabajo de corte casi terminado arruinado porque la pieza se movi\xf3 o cay\xf3 a trav\xe9s de la cama de la m\xe1quina en el \xfaltimo momento.\\n\\n**Soluci\xf3n**: Usa **Pesta\xf1as de Sujeci\xf3n** para mantener las piezas en su lugar hasta que el trabajo se complete.\\n\\nLas pesta\xf1as de sujeci\xf3n son peque\xf1as secciones sin cortar que mantienen tu pieza conectada al material circundante. Despu\xe9s de que el trabajo se completa, puedes remover f\xe1cilmente la pieza y limpiar las pesta\xf1as con un cuchillo o papel de lija.\\n\\nRayforge soporta tanto la colocaci\xf3n manual como autom\xe1tica de pesta\xf1as:\\n\\n- **Manual**: Haz clic exactamente donde quieres las pesta\xf1as en el lienzo\\n- **Autom\xe1tica**: Especifica el n\xfamero de pesta\xf1as y deja que Rayforge las distribuya uniformemente\\n\\nConsulta la [documentaci\xf3n de Pesta\xf1as de Sujeci\xf3n](/docs/features/holding-tabs) para una gu\xeda completa.\\n\\n## 4. Previsualiza tu Trabajo en 3D Antes de Ejecutarlo\\n\\nUna de las funciones m\xe1s valiosas de Rayforge es la vista previa 3D de G-code. Es tentador saltarse este paso y enviar el trabajo directamente a la m\xe1quina, pero tomar un momento para previsualizar puede ahorrarte tiempo y materiales.\\n\\n**Qu\xe9 buscar en la vista previa**:\\n\\n- Verificar que todas las operaciones se ejecuten en el orden correcto\\n- Revisar si hay trayectorias inesperadas o superposiciones\\n- Confirmar que las operaciones de m\xfaltiples pasadas tengan el n\xfamero correcto de pasadas\\n- Asegurar que los l\xedmites del trabajo quepan dentro de tu material\\n\\nPara abrir la vista previa 3D, haz clic en el bot\xf3n **3D Preview** en la barra de herramientas principal despu\xe9s de generar tu G-code.\\n\\nAprende m\xe1s sobre la vista previa 3D en nuestra [documentaci\xf3n de UI](/docs/ui/3d-preview).\\n\\n## 5. Usa Ganchos de G-code Personalizados para Flujos de Trabajo Consistentes\\n\\nSi te encuentras ejecutando los mismos comandos G-code antes o despu\xe9s de cada trabajo\u2014como hacer homing, activar una asistencia de aire, o ejecutar una rutina de enfoque\u2014puedes automatizar esto con **Macros y Ganchos de G-code**.\\n\\n**Casos de uso comunes**:\\n\\n- **Gancho pre-trabajo**: Hacer homing de la m\xe1quina, activar asistencia de aire, ejecutar una rutina de auto-enfoque\\n- **Gancho post-trabajo**: Desactivar asistencia de aire, volver a la posici\xf3n home, reproducir un sonido de finalizaci\xf3n\\n- **Macros espec\xedficas por capa**: Cambiar la altura de enfoque entre operaciones, cambiar m\xf3dulos l\xe1ser\\n\\nLos ganchos soportan sustituci\xf3n de variables, por lo que puedes referenciar propiedades del trabajo como grosor del material, tipo de operaci\xf3n, y m\xe1s.\\n\\nEjemplo de gancho pre-trabajo:\\n\\n```gcode\\nG28 ; Home all axes\\nM8 ; Turn on air assist\\nG0 Z{focus_height} ; Move to focus height\\n```\\n\\nConsulta nuestra [gu\xeda de Macros y Ganchos de G-code](/docs/machine/hooks-macros) para ejemplos detallados y referencia de variables.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Consejo Extra: Prueba Primero en Material de Desecho\\n\\nAunque esto no es espec\xedfico de Rayforge, vale la pena repetirlo: siempre prueba nuevas configuraciones, operaciones o materiales primero en desechos. Usa los perfiles de materiales y preajustes de operaci\xf3n de Rayforge para guardar tus configuraciones probadas para uso futuro.\\n\\n---\\n\\n*\xbfTienes tus propios consejos y trucos de Rayforge? \xa1Comp\xe1rtelos con la comunidad en [GitHub Discussions](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/discussions)!*"},{"id":"multi-laser-support","metadata":{"permalink":"/es/blog/multi-laser-support","source":"@site/i18n/es/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-01-10-multi-laser-support.md","title":"Soporte Multi-L\xe1ser - Elige Diferentes L\xe1seres para Cada Operaci\xf3n","description":"Una de las funciones m\xe1s potentes de Rayforge es la capacidad de asignar diferentes l\xe1seres a diferentes operaciones dentro de un solo trabajo. Esto abre posibilidades emocionantes para configuraciones de m\xfaltiples herramientas y flujos de trabajo especializados.","date":"2025-01-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"multi-laser","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/multi-laser"},{"inline":true,"label":"operations","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/operations"},{"inline":true,"label":"workflow","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/workflow"}],"readingTime":2.77,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/es/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"multi-laser-support","title":"Soporte Multi-L\xe1ser - Elige Diferentes L\xe1seres para Cada Operaci\xf3n","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["multi-laser","operations","workflow"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"5 Consejos para Mejores Resultados de Grabado L\xe1ser con Rayforge","permalink":"/es/blog/5-tips-better-engraving"},"nextItem":{"title":"Bienvenido a Rayforge: Software Moderno de Control para L\xe1ser","permalink":"/es/blog/welcome-to-rayforge"}},"content":"Una de las funciones m\xe1s potentes de Rayforge es la capacidad de asignar diferentes l\xe1seres a diferentes operaciones dentro de un solo trabajo. Esto abre posibilidades emocionantes para configuraciones de m\xfaltiples herramientas y flujos de trabajo especializados.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## \xbfQu\xe9 es el Soporte Multi-L\xe1ser?\\n\\nSi tu m\xe1quina est\xe1 equipada con m\xfaltiples m\xf3dulos l\xe1ser\u2014por ejemplo, un l\xe1ser de diodo para grabar y un l\xe1ser CO2 para cortar, o diferentes l\xe1seres de diodo de potencia optimizados para diferentes materiales\u2014Rayforge te permite aprovechar al m\xe1ximo esta configuraci\xf3n.\\n\\nCon el soporte multi-l\xe1ser, puedes:\\n\\n- **Asignar diferentes l\xe1seres a diferentes operaciones** en tu trabajo\\n- **Cambiar entre m\xf3dulos l\xe1ser** autom\xe1ticamente durante la ejecuci\xf3n del trabajo\\n- **Optimizar para material y tarea** usando la herramienta correcta para cada operaci\xf3n\\n\\n## Casos de Uso\\n\\n### Grabado y Corte H\xedbrido\\n\\nImagina que est\xe1s trabajando en un proyecto de letrero de madera:\\n\\n1. **Operaci\xf3n 1**: Usar un l\xe1ser de diodo de baja potencia para grabar texto fino y gr\xe1ficos detallados\\n2. **Operaci\xf3n 2**: Cambiar a un l\xe1ser CO2 de mayor potencia para cortar la forma del letrero\\n\\nCon Rayforge, simplemente asignas cada operaci\xf3n al l\xe1ser apropiado en tu perfil de m\xe1quina, y el software se encarga del resto.\\n\\n### Optimizaci\xf3n Espec\xedfica por Material\\n\\nDiferentes tipos de l\xe1ser sobresalen en diferentes materiales:\\n\\n- **L\xe1seres de diodo**: Geniales para grabado en madera, cuero y algunos pl\xe1sticos\\n- **L\xe1seres CO2**: Excelentes para cortar acr\xedlico, madera y otros materiales org\xe1nicos\\n- **L\xe1seres de fibra**: Perfectos para marcar metales\\n\\nSi tienes m\xfaltiples tipos de l\xe1ser en un sistema p\xf3rtico, el soporte multi-l\xe1ser de Rayforge te permite usar la herramienta \xf3ptima para cada parte de tu proyecto.\\n\\n## C\xf3mo Configurarlo\\n\\n### 1. Configura M\xfaltiples L\xe1seres en tu Perfil de M\xe1quina\\n\\nVe a **Machine Setup \u2192 Multiple Lasers** y define cada m\xf3dulo l\xe1ser en tu sistema. Puedes especificar:\\n\\n- Tipo de l\xe1ser y rango de potencia\\n- Posiciones de desplazamiento (si los l\xe1seres est\xe1n montados en diferentes ubicaciones)\\n- Compatibilidad de materiales\\n\\nConsulta nuestra [Gu\xeda de Configuraci\xf3n de L\xe1ser](/docs/machine/laser) para instrucciones detalladas.\\n\\n### 2. Asigna L\xe1seres a Operaciones\\n\\nAl crear operaciones en tu proyecto:\\n\\n1. Selecciona la operaci\xf3n (Contorno, Raster, etc.)\\n2. En la configuraci\xf3n de la operaci\xf3n, elige qu\xe9 l\xe1ser usar desde el men\xfa desplegable\\n3. Configura los par\xe1metros de la operaci\xf3n espec\xedficos para ese l\xe1ser\\n\\n### 3. Vista Previa y Ejecuci\xf3n\\n\\nUsa la vista previa 3D para verificar tus trayectorias, luego env\xeda el trabajo a tu m\xe1quina. Rayforge generar\xe1 autom\xe1ticamente los comandos G-code apropiados para cambiar entre l\xe1seres seg\xfan sea necesario.\\n\\n## Detalles T\xe9cnicos\\n\\nBajo el cap\xf3, Rayforge usa comandos G-code para cambiar entre m\xf3dulos l\xe1ser. La implementaci\xf3n exacta depende de tu firmware y configuraci\xf3n de hardware, pero los enfoques comunes incluyen:\\n\\n- **M3/M4 con desplazamientos de herramienta**: Cambiar entre l\xe1seres usando comandos de cambio de herramienta\\n- **Control GPIO**: Usar pines GPIO soportados por el firmware para habilitar/deshabilitar diferentes m\xf3dulos l\xe1ser\\n- **Macros personalizados**: Definir macros pre y post-operaci\xf3n para cambio de l\xe1ser\\n\\n## Primeros Pasos\\n\\nEl soporte multi-l\xe1ser est\xe1 disponible en Rayforge 0.15 y versiones posteriores. Para comenzar:\\n\\n1. Actualiza a la \xfaltima versi\xf3n\\n2. Configura tu perfil de m\xe1quina con m\xfaltiples l\xe1seres\\n3. \xa1Pru\xe9balo en un proyecto de prueba!\\n\\nConsulta la [documentaci\xf3n de Perfiles de M\xe1quina](/docs/machine/general) para m\xe1s detalles.\\n\\n---\\n\\n*\xbfTienes una configuraci\xf3n multi-l\xe1ser? \xa1Nos encantar\xeda saber sobre tu experiencia! Comparte tus proyectos y comentarios en [GitHub](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge).*"},{"id":"welcome-to-rayforge","metadata":{"permalink":"/es/blog/welcome-to-rayforge","source":"@site/i18n/es/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2024-12-15-welcome-to-rayforge.md","title":"Bienvenido a Rayforge: Software Moderno de Control para L\xe1ser","description":"Rayforge Main Window","date":"2024-12-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"introduction","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/introduction"},{"inline":true,"label":"features","permalink":"/es/blog/tags/features"}],"readingTime":1.98,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Rayforge Team","title":"Core development team","url":"https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge","imageURL":"/es/images/icon.svg","key":"rayforge_team","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome-to-rayforge","title":"Bienvenido a Rayforge: Software Moderno de Control para L\xe1ser","authors":"rayforge_team","tags":["introduction","features"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Soporte Multi-L\xe1ser - Elige Diferentes L\xe1seres para Cada Operaci\xf3n","permalink":"/es/blog/multi-laser-support"}},"content":"![Rayforge Main Window](/screenshots/main-standard.png)\\n\\nEstamos emocionados de presentar Rayforge, un software de control y env\xedo de G-code moderno y de c\xf3digo abierto, dise\xf1ado espec\xedficamente para cortadoras y grabadoras l\xe1ser basadas en GRBL.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## \xbfPor qu\xe9 Rayforge?\\n\\nEn el mundo del corte y grabado l\xe1ser, tener un software confiable e intuitivo es tan importante como tener hardware de calidad. Rayforge fue construido desde cero con un enfoque en:\\n\\n- **Experiencia de Usuario Moderna**: Construido con Gtk4 y Libadwaita, Rayforge ofrece una interfaz limpia y nativa que se siente como en casa en Linux y Windows\\n- **Funciones Profesionales**: Flujos de trabajo multicapa, vista previa 3D, integraci\xf3n de c\xe1mara y generaci\xf3n avanzada de trayectorias\\n- **Flexibilidad**: Soporte para m\xfaltiples perfiles de m\xe1quina, macros personalizados y amplias opciones de configuraci\xf3n\\n- **Desarrollo Abierto**: Impulsado por la comunidad con contribuciones bienvenidas\\n\\n## \xbfQu\xe9 hace diferente a Rayforge?\\n\\n### Operaciones Multicapa\\n\\nUna de las caracter\xedsticas destacadas de Rayforge es su flujo de trabajo multicapa. Asigna diferentes operaciones a diferentes capas en tu dise\xf1o\u2014graba detalles finos en una capa, luego corta la pieza en otra. Todo gestionado sin problemas en una sola interfaz.\\n\\n### Vista Previa 3D de G-code\\n\\nAntes de enviar tu trabajo a la m\xe1quina, visualiza exactamente lo que suceder\xe1 con nuestra vista previa 3D de G-code. Detecta posibles problemas antes de que ocurran y ahorra tiempo y materiales.\\n\\n### Integraci\xf3n de C\xe1mara\\n\\nUsa una c\xe1mara USB para alineaci\xf3n precisa de piezas de trabajo, posicionamiento e incluso trazado de fondo. Perfecto para posicionar dise\xf1os en materiales preexistentes o crear plantillas.\\n\\n### Generaci\xf3n Avanzada de Trayectorias\\n\\nRayforge incluye trazado de im\xe1genes de alta calidad, optimizaci\xf3n del tiempo de desplazamiento, suavizado de trayectorias e interpolaci\xf3n del tama\xf1o del punto para asegurar que tus proyectos salgan exactamente como se plane\xf3.\\n\\n## Primeros Pasos\\n\\n\xbfListo para probar Rayforge? Consulta nuestra [Gu\xeda de Instalaci\xf3n](/docs/getting-started/installation) para comenzar. Ya sea que est\xe9s usando Ubuntu, otra distribuci\xf3n de Linux v\xeda Snap, o Windows, te tenemos cubierto.\\n\\n## \xdanete a la Comunidad\\n\\nRayforge es de c\xf3digo abierto e impulsado por la comunidad. Damos la bienvenida a contribuciones de todo tipo:\\n\\n- Reporta errores y solicita funciones en [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/issues)\\n- Contribuye c\xf3digo mediante [pull requests](https://github.com/barebaric/rayforge/pulls)\\n- Mejora la documentaci\xf3n\\n- Comparte tus proyectos y experiencias\\n\\n---\\n\\n*\xbfTienes preguntas o comentarios? \xdanete a la conversaci\xf3n en GitHub o consulta nuestra [documentaci\xf3n](/docs/getting-started/installation).*"}]}}')}}]);